@startuml discovery
title Discovery & locating a board — ANNOUNCE (UDP) + IDENTIFY
hide footbox
skinparam shadowing false

participant "Coordinator\n(wasp_client.py discover)" as C
participant "Node A\n10.0.0.181" as A
participant "Node B\n10.0.0.183" as B

== Presence: UDP broadcast to :4243, every 5 s ==

A ->> C : ANNOUNCE\n['W']['A'][0x0C][ver][features]\n[tcp port u16][busy][board_len][board]
B ->> C : ANNOUNCE
note right of C
  ""discover"" listens for a few intervals and
  keys nodes by **source IP**. ""busy"" = a
  coordinator is connected right now.
  Broadcasts never cross a router — this
  is LAN-only (WAN unicast is on the roadmap).
end note
...every 5 s, forever — no coordinator required...

== Which physical board is 10.0.0.181? ==

C -> A : TCP :4242 — IDENTIFY [duration_s = 10]
A --> C : RESULT (empty ack)
note over A
  status LED strobes at 10 Hz for 10 s
  — "here I am"; normal pattern resumes
end note
@enduml
